 us one of two things: someone with black hair was in here at the time of murder, or someone is trying to place a black haired person at the scene of the crime. Also, no glasses shards or anything so he glasses were likely taken from him before he was pushed. \\n\\nNOTE: Nathan has brown hair and its short, hes also 30. He''s also a huge asshole. \\n\\nThe windows likely not a viable entry/exit point unless for a child. Not sure what the ages are in this house, but that likely leaves out my friend Frances and her aunt from entering or exiting using the window. the windows can be opened from the inside, so its perfectly plausible that a tiny person could've used it. Interestingly, the basement door can only be locked from the inside, meaning that whoever killed Victor needed to leave the premises in some way. The only identified entry point is the window.  \\n \\nAfter getting everyones reports, the following things are consistent:\\nFamily was together at 6:30 PM, at 6:50 Nathan went to take a phone call (hes an adult cousin so this kills my theory about him being able to fit in the window), after 8:10 ~ around 8:14 Victors light was off for bed, which is apparently early for him.at 8:20 AM, everyone is awake and theyve noticed victor is still not up so they break in the door by 9 AM. \\n\\nApparently Frances and her uncle got into a fight about her major change. She didnt tell her parents and he knows because a friend told him, and she doesnt want him snitching. She was outside by the lake at 7:55 PM. According to Nathan it can take 10 minutes to get back, which would land her at the scene of the crime at 8:05. According to Frances, Victor's light was off by 8:14, and she didn't physically go back inside until 8:20 because it took another 5 minutes for her to get the dog all situated. subtracting this 5 from the 8:20 arrival time, and confirming that both Natahn and her said Victor was ready for bed a little after 8:10 (so lets just stick with the 8:14 figure since it fits), she would have had to kill this guy in 9 minutes. \\n\\nFrances did inform us that Victor may have been cheating, he did kiss another woman on the cheek. \\n\"][\" \",\"- Include your percentage confidence for each theory\\n- Update your percentage confidence when it changes \\n- You don’t need to completely re-describe theories that have only changed a little, just refer to the earlier theory\\n- You may ignore this box if your theories have not changed at all\",\"- Include your percentage confidence for each theory\\n- Update your percentage confidence when it changes \\n- You don’t need to completely re-describe theories that have only changed a little, just refer to the earlier theory\\n- You may ignore this box if your theories have not changed at all\",\"- Include your percentage confidence for each theory\\n- Update your percentage confidence when it changes \\n- You don’t need to completely re-describe theories that have only changed a little, just refer to the earlier theory\\n- You may ignore this box if your theories have not changed at all\",\"- Frances did it (?) \\n\\n\\nInclude your percentage confidence for each theory\\n- Update your percentage confidence when it changes \\n- You don’t need to completely re-describe theories that have only changed a little, just refer to the earlier theory\\n- You may ignore this box if your theories have not changed at all\",\"- Include your percentage confidence for each theory\\n- Update your percentage confidence when it changes \\n- You don’t need to completely re-describe theories that have only changed a little, just refer to the earlier theory\\n- You may ignore this box if your theories have not changed at all\",\"- Include your percentage confidence for each theory\\n- Update your percentage confidence when it changes \\n- You don’t need to completely re-describe theories that have only changed a little, just refer to the earlier theory\\n- You may ignore this box if your theories have not chang