oot prints near the window. I can't believe I'm saying this, but I think Frances sent her dog down there through the window, the dog startled Victor, he fell, and then the dog ran away. That might excuse why there weren't any footprints in the room. Although, who would have cleaned up after the dog? It might be Nathan? I'm really stumped here. I'm gonna go crazy if its Nathan but Im gonna say the dog did it, full sending it (75% chance im correct, 25% chance I'm wrong) I am sending this theory that the dog did it and that Frances put him up to it  \",\"- Include your percentage confidence for each theory\\n- Update your percentage confidence when it changes \\n- You don’t need to completely re-describe theories that have only changed a little, just refer to the earlier theory\\n- You may ignore this box if your theories have not changed at all\"][\" \",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"I went to the mud first since it was dried. It may have been from Frances after we came in because she was outside with me when we both came in to the house at midnight. In my mind she's the only person who was out where it would've been muddy post storm, and could've committed the murder after I fell asleep. also would have made sense for the mud to dry over that amount of time \",\"Body next, just to see if there are any other clues or if I can get some fingerprints or something - perhaps more info about the shoes the person wore if mud is any indicator or anything (probably not) \",\"\",\"Since he fell on the hearth and that's likely how he died, checking the fireplace seems like the next logical option \",\"\",\"Vases next, maybe there will be glass that's different amongst the other broken stuff, and I can see whether or not those are broken glasses? \",\"\",\"Windows feel like a good next step, to determine whether or not they're a viable entry/exit point \",\"\",\"Ill investiagte the lock next, since it was smashed in and broken in real time (we know it was nathan and there were witnesses) \",\